.TH "bee-init" "1" "2011-07-25" "bee @BEE_VERSION@" "bee package management"
.SH "NAME"
bee\-init \- Create a bee file for building a bee package
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.SY "bee init"
.OP \-fh
.OP \-\-configure mode
.OP \-\-disable-versionify
.OP \-t template
.I url-to-file
.YS
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.P
.B bee-init
is used to create a file, that is run in order to build a bee package.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
.BI \-\-configure " mode"
Set
.I mode
to 'compat' if DATAROOTDIR is not supported in your build process
.TP
.BI \-\-buildtype " TYPE"
force buildtype: configure, cmake, make, autogen, perl-module, perl-module-makemaker, python-module
.TP
.B \-\-disable-versionify
Enable this flag, if you do not want that version numbers in your source url are substituted for
bee variables.
.TP
.BI -t " template"
.TQ
.BI --template " template"
Create bee file with template
.IR template .
.TP
.B \-f
.TQ
.B \-\-force
Normally
.B bee-init
warns you, if that bee file you want to create already exists. Use
.B \-f
to ignore the warning and override the old file.
.TP
.B \-h
.TQ
.B \-\-help
Print a little help screen.
.TP
.B \-V
.TQ
.B \-\-version
print version number
.TP
.B \-e
.TQ
.B \-\-exec
execute bee-file after creation
.TP
.B \-i
.TQ
.B \-\-install
execute bee-file and install software
.TP
.B \-\-prefix
.TQ
.B \-\-eprefix
.TQ
.B \-\-bindir
.TQ
.B \-\-sbindir
.TQ
.B \-\-libexecdir
.TQ
.B \-\-sysconfdir
.TQ
.B \-\-localstatedir
.TQ
.B \-\-sharedstatedir
.TQ
.B \-\-libdir
.TQ
.B \-\-includedir
.TQ
.B \-\-datarootdir
.TQ
.B \-\-datadir
.TQ
.B \-\-infodir
.TQ
.B \-\-mandir
.TQ
.B \-\-docdir
.TQ
.B \-\-localedir
Set these directories, if you do not want to install to the default locations.
.SH "FILES"
.TP
.B /etc/bee/beerc
.TQ
.B ~/.beerc
The main config files. Use these to change
.BR bee-init 's
environment variables.
